        TOPOF THE NEWS A5 THE STRAITS TIMES THURSDAY, AUGUST 6, 2020 | | | This feature is brought to you by the Ministry of Trade and Industry What to expect on your next staycation Check-in safely Hotel key cards are sanitised in an ultraviole­t box before being passed to guests to access their rooms. Contactles­s payment is encouraged to minimise contact. Check-in and check-out timings are staggered to reduce crowding. Spick and span Rooms are thoroughly cleaned and disinfecte­d before guests arrive. Extra attention is given to high-touch areas such as the telephone, door handles and remote controls. Hand sanitisers are provided to guests in their rooms. No more than five guests are allowed per room. At your service What guests should take note of: Seats and menus are sanitised before guests are seated, and again when they leave. For a safer option, guests can access digital menus by scanning the QR code provided at each table. Guests in buffet restaurant­s must order their food and drinks at their tables and wait to be served. Scan SafeEntry QR Code or allow staff to scan your ID for contact tracing Keep at least 1m apart from other people Wear a mask at all times in public areas Avoid crowded places Sweat it out Use contactles­s payment whenever possible Fitness machines and equipment are sanitised by staff immediatel­y after use. Bookings must be made before visiting shared facilities such as the gym, pool and spa. Scan the QR code for a full list of safe management measures for hotels PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW
